machine or login without a password&lt;/a&gt;. This &lt;a href="http://www.codeangel.org/article/crack_a_mac_with_firewire"&gt;vulnerability also affects
OS X&lt;/a&gt;. Right now the hack currently requires a Linux laptop, but it
could conceivably make its way to modified iPods.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To protect yourself you'll need to disable Firewire in your PC BIOS, or
&lt;a href="http://rentzsch.com/macosx/securingFirewire"&gt;on the Mac&lt;/a&gt; you will need to &lt;a href="http://docs.info.apple.com/article.html?artnum=106482"&gt;set the Open Firmware password&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">mr.rcollins</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 06 Mar 2008 06:26:00 -0500</pubDate><guid>tag:ryancollins.org,2008-03-06:2008/03/06/beware-of-that-firewire-port/</guid><category>Headlines</category><category>os x</category><category>Security</category><category>windows</category></item></channel></rss>